annotationA: Putative ATP-dependent RNA helicase me31b; Unwinds RNA in an ATP-dependent fashion (Potential). Involved in germ cell formation
annotationB: Protein bicaudal C; RNA-binding protein that is involved in oogenesis. Required for correct targeting of the migrating anterior follicle cells and the establishment of anterior-posterior polarity in the oocyte. May act as translational repressor of oskar during oogenesis. Function seems to be sensitive to small changes in expression
